               <msContents>
                  <summary>Acts of Paul, Acts of Sarabamon, belonging to Marha Krestos (9th Abbot of Dabra Libanon, floruit 1477)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="117v" facs="002">Fols 1r–117v</locus>
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1016Actsof">Acts of Paul</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="3r" facs="002">Fols 1r–3r</locus>
                     <title>Introduction</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አብ፡ እንበለ፡ ትንት፡ ህላዌሁ፡ ወዘእንበለ፡ ተፍጻሜት፡ ምኩናኒሁ፡ አልቦ፡ አመክንዮ፡ ውስተ፡ ክዋኔሁ። <gap reason="omitted"/> ንጽሕፍ፡ ገድሎ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ በረድኤተ፡ ጸጋሁ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ ልሳነ፡ ዕፍረት፡ ዘአመዐዛ፡ ለቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ በትምህርተ፡ አፉሁ<gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                     <locus from="3r" to="3v" facs="004">Fols 3r–3v</locus>
                     <title>Regarding the observance of the feast day of Saint Paul</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ስምዑ፡ ይእዜ፡ አሕዝብ፡ መፍቀርያነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘጸውዓክሙ፡ ጸጋሁ፡ ውስተ፡ ዛቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን" ቅድስት፡ ከመ፡ ትግበሩ፡ በዐሎ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ ኅሩይ፡ ወውዱስ፡ ወሰብኪ፡<gap reason="omitted"/></incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                     <locus from="3v" to="4r" facs="005">Fols 3v–4r</locus>
                     <title>Regarding his upbringing and education</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ኦ፡ ፍቁራንየ፡ ዜናሁሰ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ ንጹሕ፡ ወኅሩይ፡ ከመዝ፡ እስመ፡ ውእቱ፡ እምነገድ፡ ንጹሕ፡ ወክቡር፡ እምደቂቀ፡ እስራኤል፡ እምነገደ፡ ብንያም፡ ማእምረ፡ መጻሕፍት፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4">
                     <locus from="4r" to="5v" facs="005">Fols 4r–5v</locus>
                     <title>His calling on the road to Damascus, his baptism by Ananias, and his preaching in Damascus and the surrounding area</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወእምዝ፡ በአሐቲ፡ ዕለት፡ እንዘ፡ የሐውር፡ በፍኖት፡ ሶበ፡ አልጸቀ፡ ሀገረ፡ ደማስቆ፡ ግብተ፡ በረቀ፡ መብረቅ፡ እምሰማይ፡ ላዕሌሁ፡ ወወድቀ፡ በገጹ፡ ውስተ፡ ምድር፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.5">
                     <locus from="5v" to="7r" facs="007">Fols 5v–7r</locus>
                     <title>How the leaders of the Jews considered to kill him, how he went to Jerusalem and no one received him, of his meeting with the apostles, and how Barnabas took him to Antioch</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.6">
                     <locus from="7r" to="7v" facs="008">Fols 7r–7v</locus>
                     <title>How he traveled to various islands and arrived at the island of P̣afu and was challenged by the magician, Baryasos</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.7">
                     <locus from="7v" to="7v" facs="009">Fols 7v–7v</locus>
                     <title>How Paul and Barnabas arrived at Ṣärgen</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.8">
                     <locus from="7v" to="8r" facs="009">Fols 7v–8r</locus>
                     <title>Healing at Lystra</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.9">
                     <locus from="8r" to="10r" facs="009">Fols 8r–10r</locus>
                     <title>Paul’s vision in Ṭiro’äda to go to Macedonia; about Lydia, and how Paul and Silas were imprisoned</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.10">
                     <locus from="10r" to="10v" facs="011">Fols 10r–10v</locus>
                     <title>About the healing power of Paul and the raising of Eutychus</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.11">
                     <locus from="10v" to="19r" facs="012">Fols 10v–19r</locus>
                             <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.11.1">
                               <locus from="10v" facs="012">Fols 10v and following</locus>
                               <title>The vision of Paul in which the Lord encouraged him to minister to the Gentiles</title>
                               </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.11.2">
                               <locus from="10v" to="11v" facs="012">Fols 10v–11v</locus>
                               <title>the persecution in Ephesus</title>
                              </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.11.3">
                                <locus from="11v" to="19r">Fols 11v–19r</locus>
                                <title>how Paul healed the sick in Ephesus, became sick himself, converted all of the sick people there, and how a persecution arose from the instigation of Demetrius, the goldsmith</title>
                                </msItem>
                          </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.12">
                     <locus from="19r" to="33r" facs="020">Fols 19r–33r</locus>
                     <title>How Paul went to the city of Ḥäläb and converted the people there</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወእምድኅረ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ወፅአ፡ እምኀቤሆሙ፡ ወሖረ፡ ሀገረ፡ ሐለብ፡ ወይእቲ፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ እምአህጉረ፡ አይሁድ፡ ወረከበ፡ በህየ፡ ብእሴ፡ በውስተ፡ ፍኖት፡ ዘስሙ፡ ከዋርጥስ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.13">
                     <locus from="33r" to="39r" facs="034">Fols 33r–39r</locus>
                     <title>How Paul went to Iconium, was imprisoned, how God saved him and Skǝnṭǝs who suffered with him, how he converted the people of the city, and how he ordained Skǝnṭǝs to minister in that place</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.14">
                     <locus from="39r" to="41r" facs="040">Fols 39r–41r</locus>
                     <title>Paul’s trial before Festus and was given to Agrippa, how Agrippa sent him to Rome, how the angel of God encouraged Paul in a vision, how he set forth on a ship, encouraged the other travellers on the ship, how they arrived at Miletus, how he was bitten by a viper and suffered no ill, and how he healed the father of the governor of the island</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወእምድኅረ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ወፅአ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ እምኀቤሆሙ፡ ወሆረ፡ አድያም፡ ወሰበከ፡ ህየ፡ በስመ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/> ወአሜሃ፡ አስተዋደይዎ፡ አይሁድ፡ ኀበ፡ ፍሕስጦስ፡ መኰንን፡ መጠዎ፡ ለአግሪጳ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.15">
                     <locus from="41r" to="44r" facs="042">Fols 41r–44r</locus>
                     <title>How Paul lived in Rome for two years, how the household of Emperor Nero became followers of Paul, how Paul healed a servant of Nero called Bäṭǝriq, how Nero became angry and imprisoned all the Christians including Paul, and how Nero ordered that the Christians be burned alive</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.16">
                     <locus from="44r" to="79r" facs="045">Fols 44r–79r</locus>
                     <title>How the Lord sent Philip from Caesarea to go to Lystra and Iconium to be with Paul and how they ministered together in those cities</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.17">
                     <locus from="79r" to="99v" facs="080">Fols 79r–99v</locus>
                     <title>How Paul went to the city of Gahǝlǝya and preached there; how he met with Andrew and Peter and how they preached to the people of that city</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.18">
                     <locus from="99v" to="105v" facs="101">Fols 99v–105v</locus>
                     <title>How Paul went to the island of Mänafǝqt and preached and ministered there</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.19">
                     <locus from="105v" to="114r" facs="107">Fols 105v–114r</locus>
                     <title>How Paul went to the city of Wariqon and how he performed miracles there with Saint Peter, and how the Virgin Mary came to that place to help them in their preaching</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወካዕበ፡ ስምዑ፡ ኦ፡ አኀዊነ፡ ስብከቶ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ በሀገረ፡ ዋሪቆን። ወዘከመ፡ ጸውዖሙ፡ ለሰብአ፡ ኀበ፡ ሃይማኖተ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወዘተከሥተ፡ እመንክራት፡ ባቲ፡ ባቲ፡ ወምጽአታ፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ኀቤሁ፡ ከመ፡ ትትራድኦ፡ ወታጽንዖ፡ በስብከት፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.20">
                     <locus from="114r" to="117r" facs="115">Fols 114r–117r</locus>
                     <title>How Paul preached the gospel before Emperor Nero, how the King ordered that Paul be beheaded, how the soldiers came to execute him, how they beheaded him and how milk and blood flowed from his head; how Paul appeared to Nero in a vision and told him that he had been raised from the dead</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/> ዝንቱ፡ ስምዑ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ ወአቅደመ፡ ምህሮቶሙ፡ ለሕዝብ፡ ወይቤ፡ ኦሰብእ፡ እለ፡ ቦሙ፡ አእምሮ፡ ስምዑ፡ ወአእምሩ፡ ወለብዉ፡ ዘእብለክሙ፡ ከመ፡ ታእምሩ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.21">
                     <locus from="117r" to="117v" facs="118">Fols 117r–117v</locus>
                     <title>Concluding Prayer and colophon</title>

                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                       <locus target="#117v" facs="119">Fol. 117v</locus>
                       <foreign xml:lang="gez">
                         ለዘ፡ እጽሐፈ፡ ዘንተ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ አቡነ፡ መርሐ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ተዘኪሮ፡<gap reason="omitted"/>

                       </foreign>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <locus from="118r" to="130v" facs="119">Fols 118r–130v</locus>
                     <title>Acts of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12505Sarabamon">Sārābāmon</persName> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገድለ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሰራባሞን፡</foreign>
                     </title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.1">
                     <locus from="118r" to="120r" facs="119">Fols 118r–120r</locus>
                     <title>Introduction</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/> ድርሳን፡ ዘተናገረ፡ አቡነ፡ ቅዱስ፡ እለ፡ ስክንድሮስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዘህገረ፡ ዐባይ፡ እለ፡ እስክንድርያ፡ በእንተ፡ ብፁዕ፡ ወቅዱስ፡ ሰማዕት፡ ሰራባሞን፡ ኤጲስ፡ ቆጶስ፡ ዘህገረ፡ ነቅዩስ፡ ዘይትነበብ፡ በዕለተ፡ ተዝካሩ፡ ንጹሕ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.2">
                     <locus from="120r" to="121r" facs="121">Fols 120r–121r</locus>
                     <title>About his parents</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">About his parents</incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.3">
                     <locus from="121r" to="123v" facs="122">Fols 121r–123v</locus>
                     <title>About his birth and conversion to Christianity</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ንግባእኬ፡ ኀበ፡ ጥንተ፡ ነገር። ወሶበ፡ ተወልደ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ሕፃን፡ ሰመይዎ፡ ስምዖን፡ በስመ፡ እምሔወ፡ አቡሁ፡ በከመ፡ አቅደምነ፡ ነጊረ፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ወልደ፡ እኅወ፡ አቡሁ፡ ለእስጢፋኖስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ዲያቆናት፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.4">
                     <locus from="123v" to="128v" facs="125">Fols 123v–128v</locus>
                     <title>How our Lady Mary appeared to Abba Särabamon and commanded him to go to Alexandria to receive baptism; how the angel of God led him to Alexandria; and how the archbishop Tewonas baptized him and named him Särabamon</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወበአሐቲ፡ ዕለት፡ እመዋዕል፡ እንዘ፡ ዘንተ፡ ይሔሊ፡ ቦአ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ መቅደስ፡ መቃብረ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ወኖመ፡ ውስቴታ፡ በዐቢይ፡ ሐዘን። እስመ፡ ሐዘን፡ ይረክቦሙ፡ ለጠቢባን፡ በከመ፡ ጽሑፍ፡ በምሳልያት። ወበእንተ፡ ሐዘነ፡ ልቡ፡ ወጻሕቀ፡ መንፈሱ፡ ኀበ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወነሢአ፡ ጥምቀት፡ ቅድስት። <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.5">
                     <locus from="128v" to="130v" facs="130">Fols 128v–130v</locus>
                     <title>How the new Archbishop P̣etros ordained Särabamon bishop of Näqǝyus</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወበውእቱ፡ መዋዕል፡ አዕረፈ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቴዎናስ፡ ርእሰ፡ ኤጲስ ቆጶሳት፡ ወተሐርየ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ዲያቆን፡ ከመ፡ ይንበር፡ ዲበ፡ መንበሩ። ወኮነ፡ ፍሥሐ፡ ዐቢየ፡ ውስተ፡ አቢያተ፡ ክርስቲያናት፡ በእንቲአሁ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                     <locus from="131r" to="148v" facs="132">Fols 131r–148v</locus>
                     <title>Seven Miracles of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12505Sarabamon">Sārābāmon</persName> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተአምረ፡ ሰራባሞን፡</foreign>
                     </title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.1">
                     <locus from="131r" to="131r" facs="132">Fols 131r–131r</locus>
                     <title>First Miracle of Särabamon: How Saint Särabamon healed the sick like the apostles, by his shadow and the hem of his garment</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">አሐዱ፡ ተአምሪሁ፡ ለብፁዕ፡ ወቅዱስ፡ አባ፡ ሰረባሞን፡ በረከቱ፡ ትኩን፡ ላዕሌነ፡ አሜን። እወጥን፡ ወእዜኑ፡ መንክራቲሁ፡ ዘገብረ፡ በእደዊሁ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ ቅዱስ ሰረባሞን፡</incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.2">
                     <locus from="131r" to="132r" facs="132">Fols 131r–132r</locus>
                     <title>Second Miracle of Särabamon: How Saint Särabamon admonished the wealthy people of the city of Romǝndǝyos to help the poor in their time of hunger, and how the wealthy people helped the poor of the city</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ካልእ፡ ተአምሪሁ፡ ለብፁዕ፡ ሰማዕት፡ አባ፡ ሰራባሞን፡ ትዕቀበነ፡ ትንብልናሁ፡ አሜን። ወኮነ፡ ራኀበ፡ ዐቢየ፡ በሀገረ፡ ሮምንድዮስ፡ በከመ፡ ኮነ፡ በሰማርያ፡ በመዋዕለ፡ ኤልሳዕ፡ ነቢይ፡<gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.3">
                     <locus from="132r" to="133v" facs="133">Fols 132r–133v</locus>
                     <title>Third Miracle of Särabamon: How Saint Särabamon prayed for the destruction of the temple of Apollo and how the temple was inundated by water</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወካዕበ፡ እፈቅድ፡ እንግርክሙ፡ ዘንተ፡ ሣልሰ፡ ተአምረ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሰራባሞን፡ በረከቱ፡ ትኩን፡ ላዕሌነ፡ አሜን። ወኮነ፡ በውእቱ፡ መዋዕል፡ ሐጉለ፡ ጣዖት፡ ብዙኅ፡ ወኮኑ፡ ገነውቱ፡ አብዕልተ፡ እስመ፡ ይሁቡ፡ ጸባሕተ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.4">
                     <locus from="133v" to="134r" facs="135">Fols 133v–134r</locus>
                     <title>Fourth Miracle of Särabamon: How Saint Särabamon destroyed the worship of idols in the temple of Säbin</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወዓዲ፡ እንግርክሙ፡ ራብዐ፡ ተአምሪሁ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሰማዕት፡ አባ፡ ሰራባሞን፡ በረከቱ፡ ላዕሌነ፡ አሜን፡ ወሀለወት፡ አሐቲ፡ ሀገር፡ ውስተ፡ መንበሩ፡ እንተ፡ ትሰመይ፡ ሰቢን፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.5">
                     <locus from="134r" to="141r" facs="135">Fols 134r–141r</locus>
                     <title>Fifth Miracle of Särabamon: How Saint Särabamon and other Christians were put in prison by Arias and his followers; how Saint Särabamon argued with Arias and Miliṭos and how he defeated them and led the people to orthodox faith</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ወካዕበ፡ስምዑ፡ እንግርክሙ፡ ዘንተ፡ ነገረ፡ ዘኮነ፡ እምቅዱስ፡ ኀያል፡ ሰራባሞን፡ ወገድለኒ፡ ዘተጋደለኒ፡ ዘተጋደለ፡ እስመ፡ ኮነ፡ መዋዔ፡ ወከሀሌ፡ በኵሉ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.6">
                     <locus from="141r" to="143r">Fols 141r–143r</locus>
                     <title>Sixth Miracle of Särabamon: How Saint Särabamon went to the city of Säbin, disquised as a sick person; how he entered the temple; how he helped the sick people in the temple; and led them to orthodox faith</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ሳድስ፡ ተአምሪሁ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሰረባሞን፡ ዘኮነት፡ በእደዊሁ፡ ወመንክረ፡ ለዘ፡ ይሰምዓ፡ ወዘያነብባ፡ ያፈደፍዳ፡ ስብሐቲሁ፡ እስመ፡ በእንቲአሁ፡ ድኅኑ፡ ነፍሳተ፡ ብዙኀን፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ይጸግወነ፡ በረከቶ፡ አሜን። ወሶበ፡ ወፅኡ፡ ኤጲስ፡ ቆጶሳት፡ እቤተ፡ ሞቅሕ፡ ወነበሩ፡ ምስለ፡ አብ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ አኀዙ፡ ይትናገሩ፡ በኅድአት፡ . . .</incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3.7">
                     <locus from="143v" to="148v" facs="145">Fols 143v–148v</locus>
                     <title>Seventh [mistakenly identified as the Fifth] Miracle of Särabamon: How Saint Särabamon went to the temple of Lǝlǝmǝtir; how he saw the festivals in the temple; how he prayed to God for the destruction of the temple; how the earth swallowed the temple and the people in it; and how he rebuked Christians who had gone to that temple in the past</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ኀምስ፡ ተአምሪሁ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሰማዕት፡ አባ፡ ሰራባሞን፡ ኤጲስ፡ ቆጶስ፡ ዘሀገረ፡ ነቅዩስ፡ በረከቱ፡ ላዕሌነ፡አሜን። ወአጋንንትሰ፡ ኢያርመሙ፡ እምአመ፡ ሖረ፡ ቅዱስ፡ እምኀቤሆሙ፡ ተመይጡ፡ ወቦኡ፡ ውስተ፡ ጣዖታት፡ ዳግመ፡ ወገብሩ፡ በከመ፡ ኮኑ፡ ይገብሩ፡ ቀዲሙ፡ እስከ፡ ነገዱ፡<gap reason="omitted"/>።</incipit>
                  </msItem>
                </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                     <locus from="149r" to="166r" facs="150">Fols 149r–166r</locus>
                     <title>The Martyrdom of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12505Sarabamon">Sārābāmon</persName> in the Reign of Diocletian by the hand of Awǝṭakiyonon Komos [on f. 165v the spelling is, Awkǝdidǝyanos Komos]</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡<gap reason="omitted"/> ስምዑ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሰራባሞን፡ ኤጲስ፡ ቆጶስ፡ ዘህገረ፡ ነቅዩስ፡ ዘፈጸመ፡ ገድሎ፡ አመ፡ ፳ወ፰ ለወርኀ፡ ኅዳር፡ በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አሜን፡ ወኮነ፡ በሢመተ፡ አውጣኪያኖን፡ ኮሞስ፡ ዘህገረ፡ እስክንድርያ፡<gap reason="omitted"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                   </msItem>


                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i5">
                     <locus from="166r" to="166r" facs="167">Fols 166r–166r</locus>
                     <title>Concluding Prayer, mentioning again the owner</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  </msItem>


